                </p>
                <p class=" eng invisible">
                    Chairman
                    Marcos Ayerra, was appointed by the N° 141/2015 Executive Decree, on December 17, 2015. He is a member of the board of IOSCO (entity that brings together regulators from more than 115 countries), where he is the Vice Chairman of the Growth and Emerging Markets Committee, and represents IOSCO in the Monitoring Board of the IFRS Foundation.
                    He has a degree in Business Administration from the Argentine Catholic University (UCA) and has attended the Senior Management Program (PAD) at IAE in the year 2006.
                    Furthermore, Mr. Marcos Ayerra has more than 25 years of experience in the investment banking industry, both in Argentina and abroad, in entities such as Chase Manhattan Bank, Chase Securities Inc., Infupa, Telecom Argentina and Biosidus, among others. His professional experience highlights mergers and acquisitions, project financing, issuance and restructuring of liabilities, public offering, bonds and business transformation processes.

                </p>
