                    Dentro de sus responsabilidades, tuvo a cargo la cobertura de clientes soberanos y privados en la región con foco en la originación, estructuración y distribución de deuda pública y privada, emisiones de bonos internacionales, como así también el desarrollo y estructuración de instrumentos derivados. El ejercicio de este rol, le permitió entablar relaciones con los principales emisores y reguladores de la región, al igual que con la base de inversionistas internacionales especializada en América Latina.

                </p>
                <p class="invisible">Martin Gavito, was appointed by the n° 774/2016 Executive Decree on June 15, 2016. He has a degree in Business Administration (UCA). He has an MBA in International Management with specialization in Global Finance graduated with honors. He joined the Board of the Securities and Exchange Commission of Argentina (CNV) after a vast international career path in investment banking. Mr. Martin Gavito possess an extensive experience of more than fifteen years in the financial industry which includes executive positions in New York as director of Global markets at Deutsche Bank and as Head of the fixed income team at Barclays, always focused in Latin America. Within Mr. Martin Gavito responsibilities, he was in charge of the coverage of sovereign and private clients in the region with focus on the origination, structuring and distribution of public and private debt, international bonds issues, as well as development and Structuring of derivative instruments. The exercise of this role, allowed him to establish relations with the main Issuers and regulators of the region, as well as with the main core of international investors specialized in Latin America.</p>  <p><a href="javascript:void(0);" class="switch esp">English Version</a></p>
